          <ul class="menu">
           <li class="first leaf menu-mlid-1536 menu-item-15"><a href="/academicaffairs/advising/overview" title=""><span>Advisors Council</span></a></li> 
           <li class="last leaf menu-mlid-1537 menu-item-16"><a href="/academicaffairs/advising/student-resources" title=""><span>Student Resources</span></a></li> 
          </ul>
         </div> 
        </div> 
       </div> 
       <div id="block-block-7" class="block block-block"> 
        <div class="content"> 
         <p>The Institute Advising Office is an excellent starting point for general questions related to academic advising at RIT. If any member of the RIT community--student, faculty, or staff--needs assistance with advising related issues, the Institute Advising Office is a great resource. If you are unsure of who your advisor is or have general advising questions we are here to help you.</p>
         <p>If you are looking for more specific answers about your program please contact your <a href="undergraduate-advising-offices">college advising office</a>. You can use our <a href="contact-us#form">contact form</a> to send us questions or request an appointment.</p> 
        </div> 
